Steps:

Step 1: Install Java (Prerequisite)
   -> yum update -y
   -> yum install java -y

Step 2: Create a Dedicated Tomcat User
  -> useradd srujan
  -> passwd srujan - 1234
  -> Add srujan to sudoers group
  -> create a group called tomcat and add srujan to that group
  -> change to srujan user in EC2 machine 

Step 3: Download and Extract Tomcat
  -> Visit official tomcat website
  -> download the chosen version to your EC2 machine (that will be in .tar.gz)
  -> Remove tar and zip on that file
  -> Move that file to /opt/tomcat -> This is where ideally all applications should sit

Step 4: Configure Permissions
  -> Now, verify the file permissions for this folder in /opt. It should be 755 with owner set to srujan and group set to tomcat

Step 5: Create a systemd Service File
  -> You will get error when you try systemctl start tomcat command now saying service not found. We have to fix this 
  -> create a file in the following path and fill the file as stated in chat gpt. 
             sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/tomcat.service

Step 6: Start and Enable the Tomcat Service
  -> sudo systemctl daemon-reload
  -> systemctl start tomcat
  -> systemctl enable tomcat
You will get error here. You have to change the java path in the tomcat.service file. chat gpt will give you the correct data. copy paste in that file

Step 7: Adjust Your Firewall Settings - port 8080
 In security group open port 8080 for tomcat access 

